| 3 | Create index **CONCURRENTLY** | `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_orders_user_id ON orders(user_id)` |
| 4 | Verify creation | `idx_orders_user_id` (btree) confirmed in `pg_indexes` |
| 5 | Check lock conflicts | No harmful locks (`AccessExclusiveLock`) recorded |

**Key details:**
- Used `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY` to avoid `AccessExclusiveLock` — write operations were **never blocked** during the build
- Acquired only a brief `ShareUpdateExclusiveLock` (non-blocking) at startup/end
- Build logged ~180 seconds (vs. ~15 min blocking, plus write starvation risk)
- No duplicate indexes detected before creation
- No lock conflicts recorded after completion
